1
00:00:52,051 --> 00:00:56,973
ALL CHARACTERS, ORGANIZATIONS,
AND PLACES ARE FICTITIOUS

2
00:00:57,057 --> 00:00:59,225
Lee Myeong-guk
regularly met with Jung Sang-ui

3
00:00:59,309 --> 00:01:01,061
at the Pilo-dong lab and did something.

4
00:01:01,144 --> 00:01:03,271
Are you saying they were making lemon pop?

5
00:01:03,354 --> 00:01:06,232
At first, they probably made
small batches just for Jong-soo.

6
00:01:06,316 --> 00:01:08,777
Lee Myeong-guk made it,
Park Jun-seo delivered it,

7
00:01:08,860 --> 00:01:09,986
and Won Jong-soo took it?

8
00:01:10,070 --> 00:01:12,197
Jun-seo isn't here anymore,

9
00:01:12,280 --> 00:01:14,449
so who's delivering Won Jong-soo's drugs,

10
00:01:14,532 --> 00:01:18,161
and who's running the lemon pop business
in Park Tae-jin's place?

11
00:01:18,244 --> 00:01:21,206
Doctor, it's me. I killed CEO Yoon today.

12
00:01:21,289 --> 00:01:23,166
Please get me on a ship to China.

13
00:01:23,249 --> 00:01:24,793
I'm not asking for free passage.

14
00:01:24,876 --> 00:01:27,212
I'm sending you two items
through a subway courier.

15
00:01:27,295 --> 00:01:29,672
I trust you'll find those items
worth your while.

16
00:01:29,756 --> 00:01:32,634
JUNG SANG-UI WAS DOCTOR

17
00:01:33,510 --> 00:01:34,511
You're Doctor?

18
00:01:34,594 --> 00:01:35,887
If you're curious, put your seat belt on.

19
00:01:37,639 --> 00:01:39,849
SANG-UI TAKES THE TWO DEEP
INSIDE YEONGRYUN COLD STORAGE

20
00:01:39,933 --> 00:01:41,309
AND SHOWS THEM THE LEMON POP LAB

21
00:01:41,392 --> 00:01:42,727
I'm the one who made lemon pop.

22
00:01:42,811 --> 00:01:44,479
I'm the one who got you
addicted to lemon pop.

23
00:01:44,562 --> 00:01:48,024
What did I do to deserve
becoming an addict?

24
00:01:48,108 --> 00:01:50,527
I thought since you were
so good at your job,

25
00:01:50,610 --> 00:01:52,821
you could get revenge on Jun-seo's behalf.

26
00:01:52,904 --> 00:01:55,031
You were supposed to catch Gong Jin-uk,
use him to get to CEO Yoon,

27
00:01:55,115 --> 00:01:57,784
then find me, Doctor,
and finally Park Tae-jin.

28
00:01:57,867 --> 00:01:59,994
That was my plan. With No Gyu-min.

29
00:02:00,078 --> 00:02:02,330
The taxi driver who took Jun-seo
to the construction site?

30
00:02:02,413 --> 00:02:04,165
Ask him yourself. You'll meet him soon.

31
00:02:04,249 --> 00:02:05,750
Manpyeong Port at 4:00 a.m.
two days from now.

32
00:02:05,834 --> 00:02:07,335
You can stop by Boryeong on the way.

33
00:02:07,418 --> 00:02:08,795
The old lady receiving the pension?

34
00:02:08,878 --> 00:02:11,131
-Let's do it.
-Yes, sir. Thank you.

35
00:02:11,214 --> 00:02:13,508
Didn't I tell you it'd turn out fine?

36
00:02:13,591 --> 00:02:14,926
You did well.

37
00:02:15,009 --> 00:02:19,389
For the future chairman of KH Group,
there's no need for that now.

38
00:02:19,472 --> 00:02:24,602
How can a drug-dealing punk
plan a future for KH Group?

39
00:02:24,686 --> 00:02:28,398
The biggest risk factor in this project
isn't Mayor Joo or Jong-soo.

40
00:02:28,481 --> 00:02:30,275
It's you.

41
00:02:30,358 --> 00:02:31,359
This is the police.

42
00:02:31,442 --> 00:02:33,528
THE POLICE WERE AFTER YUN-HO

43
00:02:35,113 --> 00:02:38,575
The police have already identified
Jung Yun-ho as the murder suspect

44
00:02:38,658 --> 00:02:39,826
of Lee Myeong-guk and the rice mill owner.

45
00:02:39,909 --> 00:02:42,495
If the police keep looking into this,
all of you will get suspected.

46
00:02:42,579 --> 00:02:45,331
Jung Yun-ho. We can't leave him like this.

47
00:02:45,415 --> 00:02:46,541
A RECORDING OF TAE-JIN
PLOTTING HIS MURDER

48
00:02:46,624 --> 00:02:48,710
HE SOON RECEIVES A TEXT

49
00:02:48,793 --> 00:02:50,211
YUN-HO IMMEDIATELY
GOES TO JI-YEON

50
00:02:50,295 --> 00:02:52,297
I was told there was evidence
proving you and Tae-jin

51
00:02:52,380 --> 00:02:53,590
killed Jun-seo.

52
00:02:53,673 --> 00:02:55,133
What are you talking about?

53
00:02:55,758 --> 00:02:58,177
AT THAT MOMENT,
JAE-GYEONG AND THE POLICE ARRIVE

54
00:02:58,261 --> 00:03:00,722
Jung Yun-ho took the emergency stairs.
Requesting precinct backup.

55
00:03:00,805 --> 00:03:01,931
Jong-soo, please help me.

56
00:03:02,015 --> 00:03:03,266
You need to scare Tae-jin.

57
00:03:03,349 --> 00:03:04,934
What if I tell you that I can't do that?

58
00:03:05,018 --> 00:03:08,980
I'll have to tell the world
how you ordered me to kill Lee Myeong-guk

59
00:03:09,063 --> 00:03:11,608
when he started threatening you.

60
00:03:11,691 --> 00:03:13,735
I heard what you said,
so let's talk in person.

61
00:03:13,818 --> 00:03:15,236
Jong-soo--

62
00:03:15,320 --> 00:03:17,280
BUT IT WAS A TRAP
SET BY JONG-SOO

63
00:03:17,363 --> 00:03:20,158
Chi-hyeon!
Hey, Chi-hyeon. Don't do this.

64
00:03:45,850 --> 00:03:48,144
What took you so long?
Where are the drugs?

65
00:04:10,208 --> 00:04:11,209
Is it Jung Yun-ho?

66
00:04:12,168 --> 00:04:13,169
Yes.

67
00:04:13,920 --> 00:04:15,380
Who called it in?

68
00:04:15,463 --> 00:04:19,133
He didn't want to identify himself,
so he only gave the location of the body.

69
00:04:19,217 --> 00:04:22,053
The voice belonged to someone
in his 50s or 60s.

70
00:04:22,136 --> 00:04:24,472
-Did you trace the call?
-It came from a pay phone.

71
00:04:25,765 --> 00:04:26,808
In this case,

72
00:04:26,891 --> 00:04:28,810
he likely witnessed
the body getting buried.

73
00:04:28,893 --> 00:04:31,437
He might've also seen the killer's face.

74
00:04:31,521 --> 00:04:32,981
Check all the CCTV cameras in this area.

75
00:04:33,064 --> 00:04:34,232
Yes, ma'am.

76
00:04:36,526 --> 00:04:41,030
This isn't even a hiking trail,
so what was the witness doing here?

77
00:04:41,948 --> 00:04:43,366
There's a shoe here!

78
00:05:02,385 --> 00:05:05,388
Compare this shoe to the shoeprint
left at the rice mill murder scene.

79
00:05:05,471 --> 00:05:06,472
Yes, sir.

80
00:05:10,226 --> 00:05:11,311
What's that?

81
00:05:15,273 --> 00:05:17,984
Isn't this how you collect mono maple sap?

82
00:05:19,986 --> 00:05:22,071
This must be why the witness was here.

83
00:05:47,805 --> 00:05:51,768
The biggest risk factor in this project
isn't Mayor Joo or Jong-soo.

84
00:05:51,851 --> 00:05:53,936
It's you.

85
00:05:54,020 --> 00:05:56,397
I took in the only son of a man

86
00:05:57,148 --> 00:06:01,903
who couldn't even afford to buy feed
for the ten cows he raised.

87
00:06:01,986 --> 00:06:05,448
I poured a lot of money into you
to make something out of you.

88
00:06:06,449 --> 00:06:08,826
You really are something, aren't you?

89
00:06:11,788 --> 00:06:13,414
WON JONG-SOO

90
00:06:21,506 --> 00:06:22,507
Hey, Jong-soo.

91
00:06:23,174 --> 00:06:24,175
Where are you?

92
00:06:24,926 --> 00:06:26,344
I'm working out. Why?

93
00:06:27,303 --> 00:06:28,721
You want to live long, don't you?

94
00:06:30,056 --> 00:06:31,641
We should celebrate today with a drink.

95
00:06:32,475 --> 00:06:34,393
I thought you were with Han Seong-hun.

96
00:06:34,477 --> 00:06:36,479
I'm not in the mood to celebrate with him.

97
00:06:38,147 --> 00:06:39,148
Come to Pilo-dong.

98
00:06:41,359 --> 00:06:43,319
I'll have to take a pass.
See you tomorrow.

99
00:06:43,402 --> 00:06:44,403
Tae-jin.

100
00:06:44,487 --> 00:06:47,824
Just come over.
I have something to tell you.

101
00:06:50,493 --> 00:06:51,786
Okay. I'll be there.

102
00:07:08,344 --> 00:07:10,346
Who do you think killed Jung Yun-ho?

103
00:07:11,389 --> 00:07:13,641
It could be anyone at this point.

104
00:07:13,724 --> 00:07:16,936
Won Jong-soo, Park Tae-jin, Oh Chi-hyeonâ€¦

105
00:07:18,646 --> 00:07:20,773
What's wrong with all your friends?

106
00:07:23,109 --> 00:07:24,110
But I suppose

107
00:07:24,735 --> 00:07:26,737
I'm not in a position to criticize you.

108
00:07:29,073 --> 00:07:30,366
What should we do with Chang-su?

109
00:07:30,450 --> 00:07:31,701
Let's look into him discreetly.

110
00:07:32,452 --> 00:07:34,454
-Who?
-Have Su-hyeon do it.

111
00:07:35,455 --> 00:07:36,581
Will that be okay?

112
00:07:36,664 --> 00:07:38,499
Chang-su and Su-hyeon are close.

113
00:07:38,583 --> 00:07:41,002
It'll be fine. She knows
how to maintain professional distance.

114
00:07:42,378 --> 00:07:44,464
What about tomorrow's trip
to Manpyeong Port?

115
00:07:44,547 --> 00:07:46,215
Will you take Chang-su?

116
00:07:46,299 --> 00:07:50,303
The plan is for one of us
to stow away with Gong Jin-uk.

117
00:07:51,762 --> 00:07:54,891
We need someone to go undercover
who Gong Jin-uk doesn't know.

118
00:07:54,974 --> 00:07:56,142
Let's take him.

119
00:07:56,934 --> 00:07:58,603
I just have a bad feeling

120
00:07:59,437 --> 00:08:01,314
because I don't know what he's thinking.

121
00:08:01,397 --> 00:08:03,107
We don't know anything for sure yet.

122
00:08:25,254 --> 00:08:26,297
Hey.

123
00:08:31,219 --> 00:08:32,553
What's going on?

124
00:08:38,184 --> 00:08:39,810
You sold drugs behind my back?

125
00:08:40,436 --> 00:08:41,979
You bastard.

126
00:08:46,526 --> 00:08:49,237
I had no idea you had
such tricks up your sleeve.

127
00:08:50,947 --> 00:08:52,365
Make him kneel.

128
00:08:57,119 --> 00:08:59,497
I heard these lemon-yellow pills
were all the rage,

129
00:08:59,580 --> 00:09:01,624
so I've been wanting to try them.

130
00:09:03,668 --> 00:09:05,920
But it turns out
KH Pharmaceutical made them.

131
00:09:07,838 --> 00:09:09,257
That bastard over there says

132
00:09:09,340 --> 00:09:11,551
the main component's
the same as the pills I take.

133
00:09:13,177 --> 00:09:14,845
Were you going to

134
00:09:14,929 --> 00:09:17,848
give up the location
of the factory if you got caught

135
00:09:18,599 --> 00:09:20,601
and save your own skin, you bastard?

136
00:09:22,436 --> 00:09:24,814
We should've killed this punk
instead of Jung Yun-ho.

137
00:09:27,108 --> 00:09:29,193
I thought

138
00:09:29,277 --> 00:09:31,654
that since you came from a poor family,

139
00:09:32,738 --> 00:09:35,825
you'd have a sense of justice
that I don't have.

140
00:09:37,326 --> 00:09:39,495
But look at you.

141
00:09:40,329 --> 00:09:43,708
What's in that head of yours
that made you pull something like this?

142
00:09:44,667 --> 00:09:46,168
Hey.

143
00:09:46,252 --> 00:09:47,295
Why do you think

144
00:09:48,212 --> 00:09:49,463
I've done everything

145
00:09:50,756 --> 00:09:52,675
that you told me to do

146
00:09:52,758 --> 00:09:54,552
without any complaint?

147
00:09:55,845 --> 00:09:57,096
Because we're friends?

148
00:09:57,597 --> 00:10:00,224
You know better than I do that isn't true.

149
00:10:03,436 --> 00:10:04,437
So?

150
00:10:05,229 --> 00:10:06,230
Hey.

151
00:10:06,772 --> 00:10:07,940
Other than the fact

152
00:10:08,733 --> 00:10:12,403
you're the heir to KH Group,
you're nothing.

153
00:10:13,112 --> 00:10:14,947
If it hadn't been for your father,

154
00:10:15,031 --> 00:10:18,284
I would've made sure
a stupid, greedy bastard like you

155
00:10:18,826 --> 00:10:21,287
would be too scared to look me in the eye.

156
00:10:25,499 --> 00:10:28,252
Hey, Oh Chi-hyeon.
What are you doing here?

157
00:10:28,336 --> 00:10:30,421
You were the biggest thug in Anhyeon City.

158
00:10:30,504 --> 00:10:32,798
Why are you working for a punk like him?

159
00:10:32,882 --> 00:10:34,717
Because you're best friends?

160
00:10:34,800 --> 00:10:36,594
You're doing it for the money, right?

161
00:10:45,061 --> 00:10:46,062
It hurts, right?

162
00:10:46,145 --> 00:10:47,980
Does it hurt?

163
00:10:48,522 --> 00:10:50,608
They say you can't breathe
if you get hit right here.

164
00:10:50,691 --> 00:10:53,110
So does it hurt, you bastard?

165
00:10:53,194 --> 00:10:54,862
I'll kill you.

166
00:10:56,197 --> 00:10:57,365
So tell me.

167
00:10:57,448 --> 00:11:00,117
Does it feel good to get this
off your chest after 20 years?

168
00:11:00,201 --> 00:11:01,202
Tae-jin.

169
00:11:01,827 --> 00:11:04,538
How does that
change anything, you bastard?

170
00:11:05,539 --> 00:11:07,583
It changes nothing.

171
00:11:07,667 --> 00:11:08,668
Does it change

172
00:11:08,751 --> 00:11:11,587
how you sold drugs behind my back
or the fact that I'm rich?

173
00:11:13,130 --> 00:11:14,632
Where's the money?

174
00:11:14,715 --> 00:11:16,675
Where's the money you made
selling my drugs?

175
00:11:19,553 --> 00:11:21,013
Zero, six, one, seven.

176
00:11:22,348 --> 00:11:23,349
What?

177
00:11:23,432 --> 00:11:25,434
Zero, six, one, seven.

178
00:11:26,102 --> 00:11:28,104
Those are the first four digits
of the password.

179
00:11:29,647 --> 00:11:31,482
I don't know the last four digits.

180
00:11:31,565 --> 00:11:32,566
Why?

181
00:11:34,527 --> 00:11:37,655
Because Park Jun-seo
didn't tell anyone before he died.

182
00:11:38,697 --> 00:11:41,742
What are you saying, you bastard?
Tell me the truth!

183
00:11:41,826 --> 00:11:43,035
That money?

184
00:11:44,120 --> 00:11:45,830
Nobody can access it.

185
00:11:46,622 --> 00:11:50,084
Unless Park Jun-seo comes back alive,
nobody will ever access it!

186
00:11:51,419 --> 00:11:52,545
Do you understand?

187
00:11:55,965 --> 00:11:58,342
Hey!

188
00:11:59,176 --> 00:12:00,553
Is that bastard telling the truth?

189
00:12:01,262 --> 00:12:03,764
Park Jun-seo was the only one
who knew the last four digits?

190
00:12:11,397 --> 00:12:15,484
You and Jun-seo tried to be equals
out of friendship or whatever

191
00:12:15,568 --> 00:12:17,027
and made a damn mess of things.

192
00:12:17,653 --> 00:12:20,030
This is why people
need to know their place!

193
00:12:21,574 --> 00:12:24,076
Why the hell would you split the password?

194
00:12:24,160 --> 00:12:25,244
You damn idiots.

195
00:12:28,205 --> 00:12:29,540
Are you laughing?

196
00:12:31,292 --> 00:12:32,293
Jong-soo.

197
00:12:34,128 --> 00:12:35,129
Whoâ€¦

198
00:12:36,297 --> 00:12:37,882
do you think pushed him?

199
00:12:43,888 --> 00:12:45,055
Go get the drugs.

200
00:12:45,139 --> 00:12:46,390
What?

201
00:12:47,266 --> 00:12:48,350
Those drugs you sold.

202
00:12:48,434 --> 00:12:50,394
You sold them without knowing
what they could do to you.

203
00:12:51,187 --> 00:12:53,939
You should've tested them
before selling them, you bastard.

204
00:12:54,940 --> 00:12:55,941
Go get it right now!

205
00:12:57,318 --> 00:12:59,487
Jong-soo, what are you going to do?

206
00:12:59,570 --> 00:13:01,322
You're going to record him taking drugs.

207
00:13:01,864 --> 00:13:03,741
You'll record his eyes
rolling back in his head

208
00:13:03,824 --> 00:13:06,327
and how he crawls on all fours
begging for more drugs.

209
00:13:06,994 --> 00:13:09,121
Then he won't try anything stupid again.

210
00:13:12,833 --> 00:13:13,876
I said go get it.

211
00:13:16,629 --> 00:13:17,922
Damn it.

212
00:13:23,594 --> 00:13:25,012
The same goes for you.

213
00:13:26,222 --> 00:13:29,517
You should've told me
about this from the start.

214
00:13:30,184 --> 00:13:32,978
Why did you try to impress him
when I'm the one who pays you?

215
00:13:34,813 --> 00:13:37,149
Let's have you sample
the drug you made too.

216
00:13:46,992 --> 00:13:47,993
Hey, Tae-jin.

217
00:13:48,077 --> 00:13:49,495
Just so you know,

218
00:13:50,996 --> 00:13:53,832
if it hadn't been for my old man,
I wouldn't have befriended you either.

219
00:13:55,793 --> 00:13:58,254
I hate smart guys like you

220
00:13:59,129 --> 00:14:00,339
who are full of themselves.

221
00:14:02,049 --> 00:14:04,718
"What did Tae-jin say?"

222
00:14:05,928 --> 00:14:07,137
"Do as Tae-jin says."

223
00:14:07,221 --> 00:14:08,764
"Be more like Tae-jin."

224
00:14:10,391 --> 00:14:12,226
I was sick of it too.

225
00:14:13,352 --> 00:14:14,562
But you know what?

226
00:14:15,396 --> 00:14:16,605
I still tried

227
00:14:17,815 --> 00:14:20,150
to get along with you no matter what.

228
00:14:23,195 --> 00:14:24,780
It sometimes made me feel good

229
00:14:25,990 --> 00:14:27,658
knowing I could order around

230
00:14:29,285 --> 00:14:30,870
someone as smart as you.

231
00:14:32,955 --> 00:14:34,540
But the last straw for me

232
00:14:35,708 --> 00:14:37,334
was when you tried to become me.

233
00:14:39,169 --> 00:14:42,339
Won Chang-ho has
only one son, and that's me!

234
00:14:45,301 --> 00:14:48,262
That's why you ended up like this today.

235
00:14:50,264 --> 00:14:53,017
It's in the classroom creed
that my father created.

236
00:14:55,227 --> 00:14:58,439
"We will always fulfill our duties."

237
00:15:00,107 --> 00:15:01,150
Did you forget that?

238
00:15:25,215 --> 00:15:26,342
Jong-soo.

239
00:15:28,344 --> 00:15:29,345
Jong-soo.

240
00:15:30,679 --> 00:15:32,097
Jong-soo!

241
00:15:47,738 --> 00:15:49,323
So what happens now?

242
00:15:55,496 --> 00:15:56,497
They're all going down.

243
00:15:57,998 --> 00:15:59,124
What about me?

244
00:15:59,625 --> 00:16:02,753
You'll have to take me down, too,
if you want to be safe.

245
00:16:31,365 --> 00:16:32,366
Give me your phone.

246
00:16:36,412 --> 00:16:37,413
Hand it over.

247
00:17:12,322 --> 00:17:13,407
Sang-ui.

248
00:17:13,490 --> 00:17:15,576
I'll give you 12 hours.

249
00:17:16,410 --> 00:17:20,080
If you have any photos or recordings,
destroy them and leave the country.

250
00:17:21,540 --> 00:17:22,958
I'll call you when it's all over.

251
00:17:25,002 --> 00:17:27,588
This isn't a threat.
It's your last chance.

252
00:17:37,139 --> 00:17:38,182
Joo-song.

253
00:17:44,021 --> 00:17:45,439
